    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>remaining beetroot wedges </strong>to a <strong>food processor </strong>with <strong>half</strong> the <strong>drained chickpeas</strong> (you'll use the rest later!), your <strong>tahini </strong>and a squeeze of <strong>lemon juice</strong></p><p>Add 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong>,<strong> </strong>1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]<strong> </span>cold<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>water </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and blitz until smooth – this is your <strong>beetroot hummus</strong></p>",
